    Create namespace visibility Kyverno policy (#6929)
    
    * Create namespace visibility Kyverno policy
    
    This commit adds a Kyverno policy that modifies the
    konflux-ci.dev/visibility label on any tenant namespace when a
    RoleBinding for the system:authenticated group, with a role reference
    to the konflux-viewer-user-actions ClusterRole, is updated. When the
    RoleBinding is created or updated, the label is set to 'public'; when
    the RoleBinding is deleted, the label is set to 'private'. The policy is
    currently only added to the staging clusters for testing and assumes
    tenant clusters are automatically created with the
    konflux-ci.dev/visibility=private label.
    
    * Add tests for namespace visibility Kyverno policy
    
    This commit adds a Chainsaw tests for the namespace visibility Kyverno
    policy that cover the following scenarios:
    * A tenant namespace has a RoleBinding for the system:authenticated
      group and has a visibility of 'public'
    * A tenant namespace does not have a RoleBinding for the
      `system:authenticated`` group and has a visibility of 'private'
    * A non-tenant namespace does not have a visibility label applied
    * A tenant namespace starts off with a visibility of 'private', gains a
      RoleBinding for the `system:authenticated`` group and gets a
      visibility of 'public'
    * A non-tenant namespace has no visibility, becomes a tenant namespace,
      and gets a visibility of 'private'
    * A tenant namespace has a RoleBinding for the system:authenticated
      group with a non-ClusterRole role reference and has a visibility of
      'private'
    * A tenant namespace has a RoleBinding for the system:authenticated
      group with the wrong role reference and has a visibility of 'private'

