    Increase defrag threshold to 30% (#6478)
    
    Having a threshold of 15% is too aggressive causing unnecessary
    defragmentation when DB size is < 4GB. At 4 GB, 15% means defrag will
    happen as soon as 607MB is reclaimable. There is not point defragmenting
    for 607MB when DB size is at 50% capacity.
    
    Increase the threshold to 30% to reduce defrag when DB size in not even
    50%. When DB is larger 60-70%, this is where we need to more
    aggressively defrag and this is happening due to other condition where
    we do it if 1GB is reclaimable.
    
    KFLUXINFRA-1644
    
    Signed-off-by: Hugo Ares <hares@redhat.com>

