    Deploy backup on clusters with backup label only (#3675)
    
    With the addition of EaaS clusters, the backup need to deployed only on
    host and member clusters, in other words all clusters except Eaas.
    
    ArgoCD ApplicationSet cluster generators does not support or condition
    to match `host` or `member` labels. For that reason, a new label named
    'appstudio.redhat.com/backup' was added to all clusters where we need
    backup, i.e. host and members, see [1].
    
    Change backup ApplicationSet to deploy on clusters with that new label.
    Since all application set defined in argo-cd-apps/base/all-clusters are
    getting a selector applied with Kustomize, adding the matchLabels in
    backup ApplicationSet only was getting overwritten by the all-cluster
    selector.
    
    To work around that issue, move backup folder out of
    argo-cd-apps/base/all-clusters and include it in both staging and prod
    overlays.
    
