    RHTAPSRE-489: Deploy repository-validator (#3494)
    
    * RHTAPSRE-489: Deploy repository-validator
    
    The repository validator is an admission webhook for PAC repositories.
    It will deny the creation of those if their URL isn't allowed in the
    configuration of the webhook.
    
    It's needed for the internal clusters, where we need to control which
    repositories are onboarded.
    
    Webhook repo - https://github.com/konflux-ci/repository-validator
    
    Signed-off-by: gbenhaim <gbenhaim@redhat.com>
    
    * RHTAPSRE-489: Repository validator linting
    
    Exclude the production and staging overlays of repository-validator
    from linting since they pull content from a private repository.
    
    Those overlay only introduce a configmap, the rest of the manifests
    are pulled from a public repository and they will get lint as part of
    the development overlay.
    
    This is a tradeoff between making the github action more complex
    and support fetching the manifests from a private repo or remove some
    of the linting cover from the repository-validator overlays.
    
    Signed-off-by: gbenhaim <gbenhaim@redhat.com>
    
