    feat(ASC-262): multi cluster deployment (#1247)
    
    * feat(ASC-262): multi cluster deployment
    
    This change introduce the ability to deploy StoneSoup into multiple
    clusters. The general guideline is to have reduce as much as possible
    the scripts that are needed for deployment, and relay on ArgoCD instead.
    
    The change can be split into 4 topics:
    
    ArgoCD:
    
    Instead of using Applications, use ApplicationSets with the cluster
    generator the is configured with label selectors (using Kustomize).
    
    Compose the different ApplicationSets in directories that reflect the
    role of the cluster in the fleet (e.g host, member).
    
    Hack Directory:
    
    Move the logic that responsible for creating secrets into dedicated
    scripts.
    
    Create bootstrap scripts for the different cluster types.
    
    Adjust preview.sh to work with the new ArgoCD manifests.
    
    Move the ArgoCD deployment to dedicated script.
    
    Note - This change preserves the ability to install StoneSoup into a
    single cluster for development purposes.
    
    Components Directory:
    
    The Gitops service requires that the openshift-gitops operator will be
    installed in the cluster. Deploy the subscription as part of the
    deployment of the Gitops service.
    
    The ArgoCD operator version was upgraded to 1.7 since it contained
    a fix to a bug affected the deployment of multiple clusters
    GITOPS-2015
    
    Docs:
    
    Update the docs according to the changes. The multi cluster docs
    are still not complete. Those can be completed when we sort out
    the injection of secrets to the clusters.
    
    Out of scope:
    
    - Vault deployment in member clusters
    - Injecting the required secrets for the StoneSoup components
      from a central location.
    
