    Two scripts to help get SSL working for chains
    
    1. Add CA certs accessible in the chains controller to prevent TLS
    failures when running chains in a local cluster
    
    A workaround based on https://docs.engineering.redhat.com/x/zFp-Dw .
    There's probably better ways to solve the problem, but this gets
    things working so I think it's okay for now until we have a better
    solution.
    
    2. Trust local cluster ingress cert to allow cosign to access the
    local registry if it's using a self-signed cert
    
    It might be possible to do the docker login without SSL and then run
    cosign with --allow-insecure-registry, but it's easier to avoid all
    that by trusting the local cluster's ingress cert.
    
    This is probably not needed or wanted for non-local clusters that
    already have real trusted certs, but it should be a useful
    convenience for local development using CRC.
    
    JIRA: HACBS-47

